{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e407f9e2-54e9-497a-b900-531e7268472a","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Update package references** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n   <!-- Add -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Upgrade xUnit packages** — MTP requires **xUnit v3**:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Replace xunit 2.9.3 -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add the MTP property** to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n### Key notes\n- **xUnit v2 → v3 is required.** MTP is only supported by xUnit v3 (`xunit.v3` / `xunit.v3.runner.mtp`). There is no MTP runner for xUnit v2.\n- xUnit v3 has some API changes (e.g., `Assert.Equal` for collections, `TheoryData<T>` changes). Review the [xUnit v3 migration guide](https://xunit.net/docs/getting-started/v3/migration) for breaking changes.\n- You can optionally remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` if it's referenced — MTP doesn't need it, though it's harmless to keep.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"57c7d8be-5d79-4386-9df1-37aa79023da4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using `xunit.runner.visualstudio`) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":473,"requestId":"5C2A:764A5:7E204:9E6B6:69F549ED"},"id":"73db0999-bf1e-4c0d-bdd9-a8f16c977494","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:48:56.053Z","parentId":"ebf84a76-9bec-46a9-828c-9059b79d468b"}
